WEBVTT

01:29.924 --> 01:31.676
INDIANS!

01:33.344 --> 01:35.221
INDIANS!

01:42.103 --> 01:43.897
[RINGS BELL]

01:56.075 --> 01:57.619
BENJAMIN,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

01:57.786 --> 01:59.621
INDIANS, MR. INGALLS,
A WHOLE BUNCH OF THEM!

01:59.788 --> 02:01.414
ALL RIGHT, NOW,
JUST TAKE IT EASY.

02:01.581 --> 02:02.916
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU SAW, BUT IT COULDN'T
HAVE BEEN INDIANS.

02:03.082 --> 02:04.751
THEN WHAT IN
THE HECK ARE THEM?

02:55.718 --> 02:59.639
I AM LITTLE CROW,
SON OF LONG ELK.

02:59.806 --> 03:04.018
WE ARE SANTEE--
PEOPLE OF THE LAKOTA.

03:04.185 --> 03:05.603
WE COME IN PEACE.

03:05.770 --> 03:06.980
WHAT DO YOU WANT HERE?

03:07.146 --> 03:10.525
THERE IS MUCH
SORROW AND TROUBLE
AMONG MY PEOPLE.

03:10.692 --> 03:13.570
WE ARE MOVING NORTH
TO A NEW LAND.

03:13.736 --> 03:15.738
WE HAVE STOPPED

03:15.905 --> 03:19.492
ONLY BECAUSE WE HAVE NEED
OF A WHITE MAN'S DOCTOR.

03:19.659 --> 03:22.954
I'M THE DOCTOR HERE.
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

03:23.121 --> 03:24.664
JUST A MINUTE, DOC.

03:24.831 --> 03:28.209
YOU DO NOT
HAVE TO DO NOTHIN'
FOR THESE SAVAGES.

03:28.376 --> 03:31.337
THERE'S ONLY 3.
WE CAN HANDLE THEM!

03:31.504 --> 03:33.214
NOW, HOLD ON, MacGREGOR.

03:33.381 --> 03:36.843
I THINK YOU'D BEST
LEARN HOW TO COUNT.

04:01.868 --> 04:04.162
Charles:
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU CAME IN PEACE.

04:04.329 --> 04:06.080
AND SO WE HAVE.

04:06.247 --> 04:08.583
MY BRAVES ONLY WATCH...

04:08.750 --> 04:11.169
TO SEE YOUR FRIENDLINESS.

04:12.045 --> 04:14.714
I'LL GET
MY MEDICAL BAG.

04:14.881 --> 04:17.258
Charles: I'LL GO
WITH YOU, DOC.

05:10.144 --> 05:13.356
[MAN CHANTING]

05:50.101 --> 05:52.645
[CHANTING]

06:22.967 --> 06:24.969
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HE WAS YOUR CHIEF.

06:25.136 --> 06:28.514
LONG ELK IS MY FATHER...
AND CHIEF OF OUR PEOPLE.

06:28.681 --> 06:30.933
HOW LONG HAS HE
BEEN THIS WAY?

06:31.100 --> 06:32.435
TWO DAYS PAST.

06:32.602 --> 06:35.813
YOUR FATHER HAS
SUFFERED AN APOPLECTIC
STROKE...

06:35.980 --> 06:37.398
A VERY SERIOUS ONE.

06:37.565 --> 06:39.692
HE'S LUCKY TO BE ALIVE.

06:39.859 --> 06:41.778
WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

06:41.944 --> 06:44.697
A CLOT HAS FORMED
IN A BLOOD VESSEL
IN HIS BRAIN.

06:44.864 --> 06:46.240
IT'S BLOCKED
THE FLOW OF BLOOD.

06:46.407 --> 06:49.285
IT'S CAUSED HIS
LOSS OF MOVEMENT
AND SPEECH.

06:49.452 --> 06:51.162
HE MAY RECOVER...

06:51.329 --> 06:53.706
OR HE COULD HAVE
ANOTHER ATTACK.

06:53.873 --> 06:55.166
IF HE DOES--

06:55.333 --> 06:56.667
WHEN CAN HE TRAVEL?

06:56.834 --> 06:57.919
HE CAN'T.

06:58.086 --> 06:59.962
HE MUST.
WE MUST GO ON.

07:00.129 --> 07:04.967
IF HE CONTINUES
THIS FORCED MARCH,
IT WILL KILL HIM.

07:07.011 --> 07:08.971
LITTLE CROW,
DID YOU JUMP
THE RESERVATION?

07:09.138 --> 07:10.932
OUR PEOPLE WERE STARVING.

07:11.099 --> 07:12.725
THERE WAS NOTHING TO HUNT.

07:12.892 --> 07:14.894
HOW CAN THAT BE?
I THOUGHT THE GOVERNMENT
JUST GAVE THE INDIANS

07:15.061 --> 07:16.771
ANOTHER BIG PIECE OF LAND
OR SOMETHING.

07:16.938 --> 07:20.858
YOUR GOVERNMENT
GIVES THE INDIANS LAND
NO ONE ELSE WANTS.

07:21.025 --> 07:24.862
IF IT WERE GOOD LAND,
THEY WOULD KEEP IT.

07:27.031 --> 07:29.575
WE WILL NOT GO BACK.

07:31.410 --> 07:33.746
I'VE DONE ALL I CAN
FOR HIM NOW.

07:33.913 --> 07:36.874
WHAT HE NEEDS NOW
IS REST, FOOD,
AND TIME.

07:37.041 --> 07:39.418
MOST OF ALL, TIME.

07:39.585 --> 07:41.838
I'LL BE BACK AGAIN
TOMORROW.

07:49.762 --> 07:52.515
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

08:15.121 --> 08:17.165
[MAN SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

08:28.426 --> 08:29.927
Benjamin: HEY, DOC,
MR. INGALLS!

08:30.094 --> 08:31.804
MacGREGOR'S CALLED
A TOWN MEETING UP
AT THE CHURCH!

08:31.971 --> 08:33.848
Charles: THANK YOU,
BENJAMIN!

08:39.729 --> 08:42.315
[CHATTER]

08:42.481 --> 08:43.357
Man: THEY'RE HERE!

08:43.524 --> 08:44.817
HOW MANY OF THEM
ARE THERE, DOC?

08:44.984 --> 08:46.819
HEY, DOC,
WE GONNA FIGHT?

08:46.986 --> 08:47.987
Man: ALL RIGHT,
JUST QUIET DOWN NOW.

08:48.154 --> 08:50.489
EVERYBODY QUIET DOWN!
QUIET DOWN!

08:50.656 --> 08:53.159
Dr. Baker: IF YOU'LL
ALL BE QUIET FOR
JUST A MINUTE,

08:53.326 --> 08:55.578
I'LL TRY TO EXPLAIN
WHAT HAPPENED.

08:55.745 --> 08:57.079
ALL RIGHT, DOC.

08:57.246 --> 08:59.165
WHAT'S GOING ON
OUT THERE?

08:59.332 --> 09:00.750
IT'S THEIR CHIEF.

09:00.917 --> 09:02.710
HE'S SICK,
AND HE NEEDS MY--

09:02.877 --> 09:04.837
MacGregor:
WHAT'S HE GOT?
IS IT CATCHING?

09:05.004 --> 09:06.631
[ALL TALKING AT ONCE]

09:06.797 --> 09:08.549
NO! NO, NO, NO!

09:08.716 --> 09:10.635
NO, IT'S NOTHING
LIKE THAT.

09:10.801 --> 09:14.138
YOU CANNOT GO
DOCTORIN' NO INJUN!

09:14.305 --> 09:15.973
LET HIM GET
A COLORED DOCTOR!

09:16.140 --> 09:17.141
[PEOPLE
SHOUTING AGREEMENT]

09:17.308 --> 09:18.684
THE MURDERING SAVAGES!

09:18.851 --> 09:20.269
[ALL TALKING AT ONCE]

09:20.436 --> 09:21.896
WAIT A MINUTE!

09:22.063 --> 09:23.231
WAIT A MINUTE!

09:23.397 --> 09:25.483
WE DON'T KNOW
THEY CAME HERE
TO KILL ANYBODY.

09:25.650 --> 09:27.944
THEY CAME HERE IN PEACE,
JUST ASKING FOR HELP.

09:28.110 --> 09:31.030
LOOK, IF YOU COULD'VE
JUST GONE OUT THERE
AND SEEN THEM--

09:31.197 --> 09:33.699
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT INDIANS,
INGALLS?

09:33.866 --> 09:36.118
YOU WERE NOT HERE
WHEN THE SETTLERS
WERE MASSACRED.

09:36.285 --> 09:37.245
THAT'S RIGHT!

09:37.411 --> 09:39.163
YOU'RE RIGHT!
I WASN'T HERE.

09:39.330 --> 09:42.208
I WASN'T HERE TO SEE
THE WHITES HANG HUNDREDS
OF INDIANS, EITHER.

09:42.375 --> 09:43.876
DON'T LISTEN
TO HIM!

09:44.043 --> 09:46.379
I'M ALL FOR
WIPING THEM OUT!

09:46.545 --> 09:48.047
Men: YEAH! LET'S GO!

09:48.214 --> 09:49.382
RIGHT!
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

09:49.548 --> 09:51.634
I'M WITH YOU!
YEAH! WIPE THEM OUT!

09:51.801 --> 09:54.053
ALL RIGHT!
LET'S GET OUR GUNS!

09:54.220 --> 09:56.430
WE'LL GET THEM ALL
BEFORE DARK!

09:56.597 --> 09:59.392
[ALL TALKING AT ONCE]

10:36.262 --> 10:38.097
THEY'RE CAMPED
OVER THE NEXT RISE.

10:38.264 --> 10:40.099
JUST REMEMBER
THEY'RE INDIANS!

10:40.266 --> 10:43.185
THEY'RE NO DIFFERENT
THAN THE ONES THAT
KILLED OUR LOVED ONES.

10:43.352 --> 10:44.729
LET'S GO!

11:05.124 --> 11:07.043
BLOODY COWARDS!

11:48.084 --> 11:50.795
OH, DARLING,
DON'T BE FRIGHTENED.

12:23.327 --> 12:26.080
I'LL GET THE TEAM
UNHITCHED AND INTO
THE BARN, JUST IN CASE.

12:26.247 --> 12:27.998
GOOD IDEA.

12:39.385 --> 12:40.719
CAN I HELP?

12:40.886 --> 12:44.223
THANK YOU, CAROLINE.
WE'LL BE FINE.

12:45.724 --> 12:49.353
I'LL JUST GIVE CHARLES
A HAND IN THE BARN, THEN.

12:54.900 --> 12:56.026
I'LL HEAT UP
THE COFFEE.

12:56.193 --> 12:57.528
THANK YOU.

12:57.695 --> 13:00.531
PA, IS HE A CHIEF?
AN HONEST-TO-GOODNESS
INDIAN CHIEF?

13:00.698 --> 13:02.867
YEAH, HALF-PINT.
LONG ELK'S A REAL
LIVE CHIEF.

13:03.033 --> 13:05.453
GEE...A REAL LIVE CHIEF.

13:05.619 --> 13:07.830
WHEN CAN I PLAY WITH
THE LITTLE GIRL, PA?

13:07.997 --> 13:09.623
I'M AFRAID YOU CAN'T.

13:09.790 --> 13:11.917
LEASTWISE, NOT OUTSIDE.

13:12.084 --> 13:13.794
Mary: WHO'D WANT TO?

13:13.961 --> 13:17.173
I MEAN,
THEY'RE ALL NOTHIN'
BUT HEATHENS!

13:17.339 --> 13:21.010
MARY, THEY MAY NOT READ
THE SAME BIBLE WE DO

13:21.177 --> 13:23.971
OR WORSHIP GOD
IN THE SAME WAY,

13:24.138 --> 13:27.433
BUT THEY'RE
HIS CHILDREN, TOO.

13:35.774 --> 13:38.986
HOW LONG DO YOU
THINK THEY'LL STAY?

13:40.571 --> 13:42.490
I DON'T KNOW.

13:42.656 --> 13:44.450
NO LONGER
THAN NECESSARY.

13:44.617 --> 13:47.870
CHARLES, ARE YOU
SURE WE'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING?

13:48.037 --> 13:49.747
CAROLINE,
I WISH I KNEW.

13:49.914 --> 13:52.791
BUT I COULDN'T
LEAVE THEM THERE
TO BE SLAUGHTERED.

13:52.958 --> 13:55.794
HOW COULD
THE RESERVATION
BE SO BAD,

13:55.961 --> 13:58.506
TO PUT THOSE
POOR CHILDREN
THROUGH THIS?

13:58.672 --> 14:01.800
WE'VE NEVER KNOWN
THE KIND OF SUFFERING
THEY HAVE.

14:01.967 --> 14:04.720
RUNNING MAY NOT BE
THE ANSWER, BUT...

14:04.887 --> 14:08.516
IF MY FAMILY
WAS STARVING, I THINK
I'D DO THE SAME THING.

14:08.682 --> 14:11.560
CHARLES, MacGREGOR
AND HIS BUNCH ARE
COMING DOWN THE ROAD.

14:11.727 --> 14:14.021
YOU STAY HERE.
I WANT EVERYBODY
TO STAY INSIDE.

14:19.568 --> 14:21.153
MacGregor: INGALLS,

14:21.320 --> 14:24.156
DID YOU HEAR THEM INDIANS
COME BY HERE TONIGHT?

14:24.323 --> 14:27.159
NO. WHY? HAS THERE BEEN
SOME KIND OF TROUBLE?

14:27.326 --> 14:29.870
TROUBLE? YEAH,
THERE'S TROUBLE.

14:30.037 --> 14:33.290
THE SAVAGES RUN OFF,
THE COWARDS.

14:33.457 --> 14:36.752
THEY HAVEN'T DONE
ANYBODY ANY HARM,
MacGREGOR.

14:36.919 --> 14:38.254
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
LEAVE THEM BE?

14:38.420 --> 14:39.838
NO, I WON'T.

14:40.005 --> 14:41.882
I'M GOING
TO FIND THEM.

14:42.049 --> 14:43.842
AND WHEN
I DO FIND THEM,

14:44.009 --> 14:47.346
THEY'LL WISH
THEY'D NEVER SEEN
WALNUT GROVE.

14:58.607 --> 15:00.317
PA SAYS IT'S A MAN'S
CHRISTIAN DUTY,

15:00.484 --> 15:01.986
WIPING OUT
ALL THOSE SAVAGES.

15:02.152 --> 15:03.696
IF IT WEREN'T FOR HIM
SCARING THEM OFF,

15:03.862 --> 15:04.947
WE'D ALL BE DEAD
RIGHT NOW.

15:05.114 --> 15:07.533
ROB MacGREGOR,
THAT'S NOT SO!

15:07.700 --> 15:09.660
MY PA SAID
THE INDIANS DIDN'T
WANT TO FIGHT.

15:09.827 --> 15:10.536
THEY ONLY WANTED
A DOCTOR!

15:10.703 --> 15:11.829
LAURA.

15:11.996 --> 15:14.498
YEAH. YOUR PA WOULD
SIDE UP WITH THOSE HEATHENS.

15:14.665 --> 15:16.542
EVERYONE KNOWS
HE'S AN INDIAN-LOVER.

15:16.709 --> 15:17.960
THAT'S RIGHT, HE IS!

15:18.127 --> 15:20.254
LAURA, COME ON!

15:21.714 --> 15:23.173
Mary: COME ON!

15:26.635 --> 15:27.344
GIVE ME THAT ROPE.

15:27.511 --> 15:29.346
MY PA IS GONNA
FIND THEM,

15:29.513 --> 15:30.723
AND WHEN HE DOES,

15:30.889 --> 15:34.059
HE'S GONNA HANG
THEM, LIKE THIS!

15:34.226 --> 15:35.561
UH!

15:35.728 --> 15:36.895
OOH!

15:37.062 --> 15:39.398
IF HANGING INDIANS
IS YOUR IDEA
OF BEING CHRISTIAN,

15:39.565 --> 15:41.692
I'D RATHER
BE A HEATHEN!

15:42.568 --> 15:44.361
Rob: MY PA
WILL FIND THEM.

15:44.528 --> 15:46.280
YOU'LL SEE!
HE'LL FIND THEM!

15:46.447 --> 15:50.034
YOUR PA CAN'T
FIND HIS WAY
TO THE OUTHOUSE!

15:58.500 --> 16:01.003
WHOA, WHOA.

16:06.342 --> 16:08.385
THAT FOOL KID.

16:30.991 --> 16:33.452
I JUST SAW YOUR SON
WANDERING AROUND OUTSIDE.

16:33.619 --> 16:34.536
ANYBODY COULD HAVE SEEN HIM.

16:34.703 --> 16:35.496
I HAD FALLEN ASLEEP.

16:35.663 --> 16:36.914
I DON'T HAVE TO TELL YOU

16:37.081 --> 16:38.832
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN
TO YOUR FAMILY
AND MINE IF HE--

16:38.999 --> 16:40.334
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

16:40.501 --> 16:42.294
IN ENGLISH.
I GOT A STAKE
IN THIS, TOO.

16:42.461 --> 16:43.462
WHERE HAVE
YOU BEEN?

16:43.629 --> 16:44.838
HUNTING, SETTING SNARES.

16:45.005 --> 16:46.090
YOU DID NOT ASK
PERMISSION.

16:46.256 --> 16:49.093
I AM A MAN NOW.
I HUNT TO FEED MY FAMILY.

16:49.259 --> 16:50.678
IS PERMISSION NEEDED
FOR THAT?

16:50.844 --> 16:53.430
YOU WERE CARELESS
AND YOU WERE SEEN.

16:53.597 --> 16:55.057
YOU HAVE ENDANGERED
US ALL.

16:55.224 --> 16:58.310
YOU ARE NOT
TO GO OUT AGAIN.

16:58.477 --> 17:01.730
I AM SORRY MY SON
WAS SO CARELESS.

17:01.897 --> 17:03.691
HE IS YOUNG
AND CANNOT SEE

17:03.857 --> 17:05.275
THROUGH HIS ANGER
AND PRIDE.

17:05.442 --> 17:07.611
PRIDE'S A GOOD QUALITY
IN A MAN.

17:07.778 --> 17:09.655
I'M NOT TRYING TO TAKE
THAT AWAY FROM HIM.

17:09.822 --> 17:11.615
I JUST WANT TO PROTECT
MY FAMILY, THAT'S ALL.

17:11.782 --> 17:15.244
WE ARE YOUR GUESTS
AND ARE GRATEFUL
FOR YOUR HELP.

17:15.411 --> 17:18.414
WE DO NOT WANT
TO ENDANGER
YOUR FAMILY.

17:21.333 --> 17:23.877
I'LL BRING YOU
ALL THE FOOD YOU NEED.

17:39.017 --> 17:40.185
WHEN WILL
DR. BAKER BE BACK?

17:40.352 --> 17:42.771
NOT TILL AFTER DARK.
IS THERE ENOUGH?

17:42.938 --> 17:44.690
YES. I MADE
SOME EXTRA BREAD,

17:44.857 --> 17:46.650
AND THERE'S SOME SOUP
FOR THE CHIEF.

17:46.817 --> 17:47.901
GOOD.

17:48.068 --> 17:49.987
LAURA, WILL YOU HELP ME
DISH UP THIS FOOD, PLEASE,

17:50.154 --> 17:51.655
FOR LITTLE CROW
AND HIS FAMILY?

17:51.822 --> 17:53.741
SURE, MA.

18:00.038 --> 18:02.291
LOOKS GOOD.

18:02.458 --> 18:04.084
THERE'S AN AWFUL
LOT HERE, PA.

18:04.251 --> 18:05.252
CAN I HELP YOU
CARRY IT?

18:05.419 --> 18:07.045
SURE.
I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.

18:07.212 --> 18:09.673
THANKS, PA.

18:16.513 --> 18:18.891
Charles: BROUGHT
YOU SOME STEW.

18:22.227 --> 18:24.146
BROUGHT YOU SOME OF
MY MA'S FRESH BREAD.

18:24.313 --> 18:26.523
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

18:30.778 --> 18:34.323
MY FATHER HAS ASKED,
"WHAT HAS BECOME OF
OUR PEOPLE?"

18:34.490 --> 18:36.283
I HAVEN'T HEARD
ANYTHING.

18:36.450 --> 18:39.411
I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN
FIND OUT TOMORROW.

18:39.578 --> 18:41.163
THERE YOU ARE.

18:41.330 --> 18:44.541
THAT BREAD
OUGHT TO GO GOOD
WITH THE STEW.

18:44.708 --> 18:48.170
AND I BROUGHT YOU SOME
OF MY MA'S COOKIES.

18:48.337 --> 18:50.756
WELL, DON'T YOU
WANT A COOKIE?

18:50.923 --> 18:53.467
MY MA MAKES THE BEST.

18:55.761 --> 18:58.263
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO BE AFRAID OF ME.

18:58.430 --> 19:01.809
SHE IS AFRAID
OF THE PEOPLE WHO
KILLED HER MOTHER.

19:12.861 --> 19:15.113
I'LL BRING THE CHIEF
SOME SOUP.

19:15.280 --> 19:17.741
DR. BAKER WILL
BE HERE TONIGHT.

19:19.868 --> 19:21.537
HALF-PINT...

19:47.980 --> 19:50.315
WHAT'S HER NAME?

19:50.482 --> 19:54.027
LITTLE CROW SAYS SHE'S
CALLED YELLOW FEATHER.

19:55.988 --> 19:57.948
YELLOW FEATHER.

19:59.616 --> 20:02.160
SUCH A PRETTY NAME.

20:03.954 --> 20:06.999
WISH I HAD ONE
LIKE IT.

20:07.165 --> 20:09.376
MINE'S SO PLAIN.

20:11.587 --> 20:13.463
"LAURA."

20:13.630 --> 20:16.049
PLAIN OLD LAURA.

20:17.759 --> 20:22.055
WELL, DARLIN',
I GUESS YOU'LL JUST HAVE
TO LIVE WITH IT, HUH?

20:22.222 --> 20:23.557
YEAH.

20:23.724 --> 20:25.392
I GUESS.

20:28.061 --> 20:30.147
[CRYING]

20:37.029 --> 20:38.447
WHEN HE SAID THAT,

20:38.614 --> 20:40.782
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

20:40.949 --> 20:42.868
I KNOW.

20:43.035 --> 20:44.995
I KNOW.

20:50.042 --> 20:52.836
WHY DO PEOPLE HATE SO?

20:56.632 --> 20:58.800
GOD ONLY KNOWS,
DARLING.

21:01.929 --> 21:03.847
GOD ONLY KNOWS.

21:20.447 --> 21:23.241
LAURA, ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT TO
COME WITH US?

21:23.408 --> 21:24.910
YES, MA,
I'M SURE.

21:25.077 --> 21:26.036
ALL RIGHT.

21:26.203 --> 21:28.246
BE SURE YOU STAY
CLOSE TO THE HOUSE.

21:28.413 --> 21:29.665
I WILL, PA.

21:29.831 --> 21:31.333
ALL RIGHT.
WE'LL BE HOME SOON.

21:45.931 --> 21:47.182
COME ON, BANDIT!

21:48.517 --> 21:50.644
[BANDIT BARKING]

22:07.786 --> 22:10.247
Laura: HOPE I'M NOT
DISTURBING YOU.

22:17.838 --> 22:19.589
FEELING ANY BETTER?

22:19.756 --> 22:22.092
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

22:23.010 --> 22:25.387
I HATE BEING SICK.

22:25.554 --> 22:28.098
BET YOU DO, TOO.

22:43.447 --> 22:45.907
BROUGHT SOMETHING
FOR YELLOW FEATHER.

22:50.162 --> 22:54.666
SOME PEOPLE NEED
MORE LOVE THAN OTHERS DO.

22:54.833 --> 22:57.461
SALLY'S ONE OF THEM.

23:00.380 --> 23:04.009
I THINK YOU'LL LOVE HER
MORE THAN I DO.

23:06.178 --> 23:08.805
SO I WANT YOU
TO HAVE HER.

23:17.105 --> 23:18.732
I BETTER GO NOW.

23:20.776 --> 23:22.944
HOPE YOU FEEL
BETTER SOON.

23:38.668 --> 23:40.045
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

23:40.212 --> 23:42.798
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

23:56.269 --> 23:58.021
Mrs. Oleson: WELL,
I MEAN, WHAT THEY DO

23:58.188 --> 24:01.566
IS MARCH RIGHT INTO TOWN
IN BROAD DAYLIGHT
AND ABDUCT PEOPLE.

24:01.733 --> 24:03.318
HOW DARE THEY?

24:03.485 --> 24:04.611
NOW, HARRIET!

24:04.778 --> 24:06.446
WELL, IT'S
THE GOVERNMENT'S
FAULT--

24:06.613 --> 24:09.491
GIVING THOSE SAVAGES
ALL THAT LAND
AND FOOD.

24:09.658 --> 24:12.369
HUH! WHAT MORE
DO THEY WANT?
LET'S SEE NOW...

24:12.536 --> 24:15.372
MR. INGALLS, THAT'S
GOING TO BE $1.53.

24:15.539 --> 24:17.040
Charles: THANK YOU.

24:17.207 --> 24:18.500
MacGregor: MRS. INGALLS.

24:18.667 --> 24:20.460
THE BLOODY SAVAGES...

24:20.627 --> 24:22.254
THEY GIVE US THE SLIP.

24:22.420 --> 24:24.089
THEY'RE HEADED TOWARD
CANADA, ALL RIGHT.

24:24.256 --> 24:26.424
YOU THINK
THEY GOT ACROSS?

24:26.591 --> 24:29.261
YEAH...YOU'D LIKE TO
SEE THAT, WOULDN'T YOU?

24:29.427 --> 24:32.097
WE SEEN SOME TROOPS.
THEY'LL CATCH THEM,
ALL RIGHT.

24:32.264 --> 24:34.766
AND WE'RE GOING TO KEEP
SCOUTING THE AREA,

24:34.933 --> 24:37.644
JUST IN CASE
THEY DOUBLED BACK--
NO NEED TO FEAR.

24:37.811 --> 24:39.729
OH, SURELY THEY
WOULDN'T DO THAT!

24:39.896 --> 24:41.398
MacGregor: YOU NEVER KNOW,
MRS. OLESON.

24:41.565 --> 24:46.611
THAT'S A FAVORITE
TRICK OF THEIRS...
THE IGNORANT SAVAGES.

24:46.778 --> 24:48.864
THEY MAY BE IGNORANT
SAVAGES, MacGREGOR,

24:49.030 --> 24:51.950
BUT THEY DID MANAGE
TO GIVE YOU THE SLIP,
DIDN'T THEY?

24:52.117 --> 24:54.202
MRS. OLESON...NELS.

24:55.078 --> 24:56.454
GOOD DAY,
MR. MacGREGOR.

24:56.621 --> 24:58.540
SEE YOU IN CHURCH
TOMORROW.

25:23.607 --> 25:27.444
MacGregor: WHOA.
GOOD MORNING, DOC.

25:27.611 --> 25:29.362
OH, GOOD MORNING,
HUGH.

25:29.529 --> 25:30.906
MRS. MacGREGOR, ROB.

25:31.072 --> 25:33.825
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER FOR YOU.

25:33.992 --> 25:36.244
BEEN AWFUL BUSY.

25:37.329 --> 25:38.788
WHY? WHAT'S WRONG?

25:38.955 --> 25:41.541
IT'S THAT GOLDARNED
CARBUNCLE, SO IT IS.

25:41.708 --> 25:43.001
IT NEEDS LANCING
AGAIN.

25:43.168 --> 25:45.128
OH, THAT MUST BE
TERRIBLE UNCOMFORTABLE,

25:45.295 --> 25:48.798
WHAT WITH ALL THAT
HORSEBACK RIDING YOU
BEEN DOING THIS WEEK.

25:51.593 --> 25:54.012
COULD YOU BE LANCING
IT AFTER CHURCH?

25:54.179 --> 25:56.014
I'M SORRY, HUGH,
I WON'T BE HERE.

25:56.181 --> 25:57.933
I'VE GOT A CALL
TO MAKE.

25:58.099 --> 26:00.185
BUT I'LL DO IT FIRST
THING IN THE MORNING.

26:00.352 --> 26:02.062
WHO'S AILING?

26:02.229 --> 26:04.064
THE WIDOW FRASER.

26:05.190 --> 26:06.358
ALL RIGHT.

26:06.524 --> 26:08.985
I'LL SEE YOU
THE FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING.

26:24.793 --> 26:25.919
Man: HI,
MR. MacGREGOR.

26:26.086 --> 26:27.337
HI.

26:41.935 --> 26:43.228
HUGH?

26:43.395 --> 26:44.896
WHAT'S WRONG?

26:45.063 --> 26:47.774
YOU GO AHEAD.
I'LL BE ALONG.

26:53.196 --> 26:55.949
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO MISS SERVICE.

26:56.116 --> 26:59.286
THAT'S NOT THE ROAD
TO THE WIDOW FRASER'S.

26:59.452 --> 27:02.956
GO ON TO CHURCH,
LIKE I TOLD YOU.

27:07.252 --> 27:09.546
TOM, I WANT
TO USE YOUR HORSE.

27:09.713 --> 27:11.214
I'LL BE BACK
IN A BIT.

27:11.381 --> 27:13.091
SURE THING,
MR. MacGREGOR.

27:13.258 --> 27:15.093
WHERE'S PA GOING?

27:15.260 --> 27:17.095
I DON'T KNOW.

27:35.322 --> 27:37.490
Caroline:
LAURA, HAVE YOU GOT
YOUR PRAYER BOOK?

27:37.657 --> 27:39.117
YES'M, I'VE GOT IT.

27:39.284 --> 27:41.119
GOOD MORNING,
DR. BAKER.

27:41.286 --> 27:42.662
MORNING,
CAROLINE.

27:42.829 --> 27:43.621
DOCTOR.

27:43.788 --> 27:45.123
MORNING, CHARLES.

27:45.290 --> 27:46.624
HOW ARE THINGS
IN TOWN?

27:46.791 --> 27:48.126
OH, FINE, I GUESS.

27:48.293 --> 27:49.794
I SAW MacGREGOR
THIS MORNING.

27:49.961 --> 27:51.963
WANTS ME TO LANCE
HIS CARBUNCLE AGAIN.

27:52.130 --> 27:53.089
OH, YEAH?

27:53.256 --> 27:54.507
I THINK I'LL MAKE
HIM WAIT AWHILE.

27:54.674 --> 27:56.259
YOU OUGHT TO LET HIM
WAIT A YEAR.

27:56.426 --> 27:57.552
[LAUGHING]

28:03.058 --> 28:03.933
DOCTOR.

28:04.100 --> 28:07.145
LITTLE CROW.
HOW IS HE TODAY?

28:07.312 --> 28:08.772
THERE'S NO CHANGE.

28:08.938 --> 28:10.190
[HORSE WHINNYING]

28:11.066 --> 28:12.442
[SLAPPING HORSE]

28:12.609 --> 28:14.694
MacGREGOR!
GET INSIDE!

28:14.861 --> 28:16.112
CAROLINE!

28:16.279 --> 28:19.074
TAKE THE CHILDREN
INSIDE! STAY THERE!

28:23.370 --> 28:25.246
HIRAM, GET HIM
READY TO MOVE.

28:25.413 --> 28:27.582
NO. WE CAN'T.
HE'S GOING
TO HAVE TO.

28:27.749 --> 28:30.502
WHEN MacGREGOR GETS
BACK HERE, HE'S NOT
GOING TO BE ALONE.

28:30.668 --> 28:32.170
WE GO NORTH.
OUR PEOPLE WAIT THERE.

28:32.337 --> 28:34.714
I'LL PUT THE CANVAS
ON THE WAGON.

29:05.787 --> 29:09.207
IT'S BEEN AT LEAST
AN HOUR SINCE WE LEFT
YOUR PLACE.

29:09.374 --> 29:10.834
MacGREGOR SHOULD
BE THERE BY NOW.

29:11.000 --> 29:12.669
I KNOW THAT.
I'M PUSHING THE HORSES

29:12.836 --> 29:14.462
AS HARD AS I CAN
WITHOUT KILLING THEM.

29:14.629 --> 29:17.632
WE'RE LEAVING AN EASY
TRAIL TO FOLLOW,
ONCE THEY PICK IT UP.

29:17.799 --> 29:20.427
I KNOW IT. WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO?

29:22.846 --> 29:25.598
I BETTER SEE
HOW HE'S DOING.

29:30.395 --> 29:32.188
YAH!

29:43.908 --> 29:46.119
MRS. INGALLS, IT'S
ONLY A MATTER OF TIME

29:46.286 --> 29:49.038
BEFORE MY MEN
FIND THOSE TRACKS.

29:49.205 --> 29:53.334
NOW, WHY DON'T
YOU SAVE US ALL
A LOT OF TROUBLE?

29:55.170 --> 29:59.382
I CANNOT BELIEVE
THAT YOU'D PROTECT
THOSE HEATHENS.

30:02.302 --> 30:05.263
I'M LOSING
MY PATIENCE NOW.

30:05.430 --> 30:09.434
I CAN MAKE YOU TELL
ME, IF I HAVE TO.

30:11.060 --> 30:13.104
MR. MacGREGOR,
IF YOU LAY A HAND ON ME,

30:13.271 --> 30:15.523
YOU'D BETTER BE SURE
YOU HAVE A LOT OF HELP.

30:23.781 --> 30:26.075
WE PICKED IT UP.
LET'S GO.

30:26.951 --> 30:27.827
MacGregor:
WHICH WAY?

30:27.994 --> 30:29.621
Man: WE FOUND IT!

30:29.787 --> 30:31.289
Second man: THEY CROSSED
THE CREEK UP THERE.
THEY'RE SWINGING NORTH.

30:31.456 --> 30:33.541
Third man: THE TRACKS
WILL BE EASY TO FOLLOW.

31:13.540 --> 31:14.832
WHOA! WHOA!

31:21.339 --> 31:23.049
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
CHARLES?

31:23.216 --> 31:25.552
NOTHING, DOC. JUST STAY
INSIDE, ALL RIGHT?

31:49.367 --> 31:51.119
WELL, GOOD DAY
TO YOU, NEIGHBOR.

31:51.286 --> 31:53.746
A FINE AND GOOD
LORD'S DAY TO YOU,
FRIEND.

31:53.913 --> 31:55.540
WHERE ARE YOU HEADING?

31:55.707 --> 31:57.166
CALIFORNIA...

31:57.333 --> 32:00.211
CHECK OUT THE MOST FABULOUS
PROMISED LAND.

32:00.378 --> 32:01.838
IT'S GOING TO BE
KIND OF A LONG TRIP

32:02.005 --> 32:03.381
WITH THOSE OLD NAGS
YOU GOT THERE,
ISN'T IT?

32:03.548 --> 32:06.884
I KNOW, BUT IT'S BETTER
THAN WALKING.

32:07.051 --> 32:09.304
HOW'D YOU LIKE
TO TRADE RIGS?

32:09.470 --> 32:11.472
HOW'S THAT?

32:11.639 --> 32:14.392
I SAID, HOW WOULD YOU
LIKE TO TRADE RIGS?

32:14.559 --> 32:17.520
I GOT NO MONEY
TO THROW IN.

32:17.687 --> 32:22.108
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT MONEY.
I'LL TRADE YOU EVEN.

32:22.275 --> 32:23.693
HOW COME?

32:23.860 --> 32:25.486
WHAT DO YOU CARE?
DON'T LOOK A GIFT HORSE
IN THE MOUTH.

32:25.653 --> 32:27.614
YOU WANT TO TRADE RIGS
OR NOT? WHAT DO YOU SAY?

32:29.532 --> 32:33.536
I SAY YES,
AND HALLELUJAH!

32:44.756 --> 32:46.507
TWO SETS OF TRACKS!

32:46.674 --> 32:48.676
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
JACK?

32:51.387 --> 32:54.390
THE WIDE TRACKS--
THEY'D BE INGALLS' WAGON...

32:54.557 --> 32:56.559
HEADING WEST.

34:04.585 --> 34:06.796
INDIAN CAMP,
DEAD AHEAD.

34:48.296 --> 34:51.174
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

34:51.340 --> 34:52.717
[LITTLE CROW SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

34:52.884 --> 34:54.969
TELL THEM THEY
GOT TO GET MOVING
AS SOON AS THEY CAN.

34:55.136 --> 34:56.888
NOT IF THEY WANT
THAT OLD MAN ALIVE.

34:57.054 --> 34:59.056
ANOTHER HOUR IN THAT WAGON,
AND HE'S A DEAD MAN.

34:59.223 --> 35:01.434
WE WILL WAIT UNTIL
MY FATHER CAN GO ON.

35:01.601 --> 35:04.687
YOU STAY HERE,
AND YOU'RE ALL
GOING TO DIE.

35:04.854 --> 35:08.191
DEATH HOLDS
NO FEAR FOR US.

35:08.357 --> 35:11.778
WE WILL TAKE
MY FATHER INSIDE.

35:11.944 --> 35:14.947
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

35:20.870 --> 35:24.665
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

35:32.882 --> 35:35.426
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

35:38.054 --> 35:39.305
LITTLE CROW,
WHEN THAT POSSE GETS HERE,

35:39.472 --> 35:41.098
I'M NOT GOING TO
BE ABLE TO STOP THEM.

35:41.265 --> 35:42.517
YOU HAVE DONE
ALL YOU COULD.

35:42.683 --> 35:44.352
YOU DO NOT HAVE
TO STAY.

35:44.519 --> 35:46.437
THEY'RE GOING
TO HAVE GUNS.

35:46.604 --> 35:48.981
WE WILL ALSO
HAVE GUNS.

35:49.148 --> 35:51.734
I GO TO MY FATHER.

36:19.720 --> 36:22.974
[TWO RIFLE SHOTS]

36:28.604 --> 36:31.357
Old man: I AIN'T GOT
NOTHIN' WORTH STEALING,

36:31.524 --> 36:34.068
BUT YOU'RE WELCOME
TO ANYTHING YOU WANT.

36:34.235 --> 36:37.530
TAKE A LOOK
IN THE WAGON...
AND WATCH YOURSELF.

36:40.908 --> 36:42.493
IT'S EMPTY.

36:42.660 --> 36:45.079
WHERE ARE THEY?

36:45.246 --> 36:47.331
I DON'T KNOW NOTHIN'.

36:47.498 --> 36:50.835
FELLER STOPS AND SAYS
HE'LL TRADE RIGS--

36:51.002 --> 36:54.422
THIS FINE ONE
FOR MY BROKEN-DOWN.

36:54.589 --> 36:57.508
I SAY YES,
AND WE GO OUR WAYS.

36:57.675 --> 37:00.052
ANY INJUNS WITH THEM?

37:01.554 --> 37:03.180
ANSWER ME, MAN!

37:06.851 --> 37:08.519
YES, SIR.

37:08.686 --> 37:11.022
LET'S GO!

37:54.732 --> 37:57.026
RIDER COMING IN. FAST.

38:02.406 --> 38:07.578
[LITTLE CROW
SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE]

38:09.830 --> 38:11.082
THEY COME SOON.

38:11.248 --> 38:13.834
YOU GO NOW.
THIS IS NOT YOUR FIGHT.

38:14.001 --> 38:15.544
YOU'RE NEVER GOING
TO GET AWAY WITH THIS.

38:15.711 --> 38:18.005
THE SUN WILL STILL
RISE TOMORROW.

38:36.857 --> 38:39.193
DOC WILL KEEP AN EYE
ON YOUR FATHER.

39:46.761 --> 39:48.471
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

39:54.185 --> 39:56.520
I THOUGHT THEY JUST
HAD BOWS AND ARROWS.

39:56.687 --> 39:57.897
SO DID I.

39:58.064 --> 40:00.441
THEY MUST'VE
STOLE THEM RIFLES
FROM SOMEPLACE!

40:00.608 --> 40:02.943
WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO DO? THAT'S A LOT OF
OPEN COUNTRY BETWEEN US.

40:03.110 --> 40:06.238
I KNOW THAT!
LET ME THINK.

40:07.615 --> 40:10.159
LOOKS LIKE WE GOT THEM
BUFFALOED SO FAR.

40:12.328 --> 40:13.788
INGALLS!

40:15.247 --> 40:16.332
YEAH, MacGREGOR?

40:16.499 --> 40:19.877
I WANT TO TALK
TO YOU!

40:22.088 --> 40:25.382
ALL RIGHT. I'LL MEET YOU
HALFWAY. NO GUNS.

40:27.009 --> 40:28.344
AGREED!

40:58.791 --> 41:01.210
ALL RIGHT, MacGREGOR,
WHAT IS IT?

41:01.377 --> 41:03.754
TELL THEM TO
PUT DOWN THEIR GUNS.

41:03.921 --> 41:06.423
WOULDN'T DO ANY GOOD.
THEY WOULDN'T DO IT.

41:06.590 --> 41:08.425
I'M GIVING THEM
A CHANCE.

41:08.592 --> 41:10.261
I THINK
YOU'RE A LIAR.

41:10.427 --> 41:13.055
ALL THEY WANT TO DO
IS GO IN PEACE.

41:13.222 --> 41:15.683
THEN WHY DO THEY HAVE
ALL THEM GUNS?

41:15.850 --> 41:19.103
TO KEEP FROM GETTING KILLED
BY PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

41:19.270 --> 41:21.605
I'M ASKING YOU
FOR THE LAST TIME,
INGALLS...

41:21.772 --> 41:24.108
YOU TELL THEM
TO THROW DOWN
THEM GUNS!

41:24.275 --> 41:26.527
OR WHAT, MacGREGOR?
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?

41:26.694 --> 41:29.655
YOU AND THE VIGILANTES
GOING TO COME CHARGING
DOWN THE HILL?

41:29.822 --> 41:31.824
YOU WOULDN'T
MAKE IT HALFWAY.

41:34.493 --> 41:36.412
YOU'D SHOOT
YOUR OWN PEOPLE?

41:36.579 --> 41:38.455
YOU'RE NOT MY PEOPLE.

41:38.622 --> 41:40.541
WE'RE WHITE MEN!

41:40.708 --> 41:42.042
YOU'RE COWARDS.

41:42.209 --> 41:44.962
THAT'S WHY YOU
WON'T COME RIDING
DOWN THAT HILL.

41:45.129 --> 41:48.382
SEE, THAT'S THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN YOU AND THOSE
INDIANS DOWN THERE.

41:48.549 --> 41:50.676
THEY'RE NOT AFRAID
TO DIE.

41:50.843 --> 41:53.429
PEOPLE LIKE YOU HAVE
DONE SO MUCH TO THEM
THROUGH THE YEARS

41:53.596 --> 41:57.057
THAT DYING DOESN'T MEAN
ANYTHING TO THEM ANYMORE.

41:57.224 --> 41:59.810
THEY'RE NOT AFRAID
OF NOTHIN', HUH?

41:59.977 --> 42:01.604
WELL, WE'LL SEE.

42:01.770 --> 42:04.148
THERE'S AN ARMY POST
EAST OF SLEEPY EYE.

42:04.315 --> 42:06.817
WE'LL SEE
HOW BRAVE YOUR
INJUN FRIENDS ARE

42:06.984 --> 42:09.403
WHEN THEY'RE LOOKING
DOWN THE FACE OF
A GATLING GUN!

42:09.570 --> 42:12.615
WE'LL SEE IF
YOU WANT TO STAY
WITH THEM THEN!

42:55.241 --> 42:56.992
THEY'VE GONE
FOR THE SOLDIERS.

42:57.159 --> 42:59.036
YOU GOT 3, MAYBE
4 HOURS AT THE BEST.

42:59.203 --> 43:00.621
WE STAY.

43:02.122 --> 43:05.209
THE SOLDIERS WILL
BRING BACK A GREAT GUN
THAT FIRES MANY TIMES.

43:05.376 --> 43:06.877
WE STAY.

43:07.044 --> 43:08.879
IF TODAY BE FOREVER,

43:09.046 --> 43:11.173
SO IT MUST BE.

43:12.633 --> 43:15.844
[CHIEF SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

43:20.266 --> 43:22.476
[SPEAKING
NATIVE LANGUAGE]

43:26.605 --> 43:28.857
[SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE]

44:22.494 --> 44:24.913
[CHANTING
IN NATIVE LANGUAGE]

44:29.793 --> 44:31.628
WHAT'S HE SAYING?

44:31.795 --> 44:34.131
"A WARRIOR I HAVE BEEN.

44:34.298 --> 44:38.177
"NOW IT IS ALL OVER.

44:38.344 --> 44:42.014
"A HARD TIME I HAVE HAD.

44:42.181 --> 44:46.894
"I AM OLD AND LIVING
AN UNNATURAL LIFE.

44:47.061 --> 44:51.982
"I STAND ON THE EDGE
OF A LIFE NO ONE KNOWS.

44:52.149 --> 44:55.069
"I AM ANXIOUS TO GO
TO MY FATHER,

44:55.235 --> 45:00.699
TO LIVE AGAIN...AS MEN
WERE INTENDED TO LIVE."

45:00.866 --> 45:03.577
IT IS HIS DEATH CHANT.

45:11.293 --> 45:14.505
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

45:54.336 --> 45:57.297
MacGregor:
IT'S RIGHT OVER
THE NEXT RISE!

45:57.464 --> 45:59.842
Soldier: YAH! YAH!

46:03.512 --> 46:05.514
READY THE GUN!

46:14.064 --> 46:15.607
GUN READY, SIR.

46:26.952 --> 46:28.996
THE COWARDS HAVE RUN.

46:29.163 --> 46:33.125
Soldier: YAH! YAH!
YAH! YAH! YAH!

46:51.810 --> 46:55.397
ALL RIGHT, INGALLS...
WHERE ARE THEY?

46:56.607 --> 46:59.443
THEY'RE IN THE MOUNTAINS
BY NOW, MacGREGOR.

47:00.986 --> 47:02.821
SERGEANT, LET'S GO!

47:02.988 --> 47:04.740
NOW, HOLD ON.
HOLD ON!

47:04.907 --> 47:07.493
ONLY GOT
A HANDFUL OF MEN
HERE, MacGREGOR.

47:07.659 --> 47:09.495
THE GUN'S
ONLY GOOD OUT
IN THE OPEN.

47:09.661 --> 47:11.497
AS HEAVILY
ARMED AS THOSE
INDIANS ARE,

47:11.663 --> 47:13.790
WE'D GET MASSACRED
TRYING TO FIGHT
IN COVER.

47:13.957 --> 47:15.751
MacGregor:
YOU CAN'T LET THEM GET AWAY!

47:15.918 --> 47:18.921
Sergeant: AIN'T A MATTER
OF MY LETTING THEM
GET AWAY. THEY DID IT.

47:19.087 --> 47:21.298
YOU WANT TO FOLLOW THEM,
YOU GO RIGHT AHEAD.

47:21.465 --> 47:23.467
ME, I'M GOING BACK
TO THE POST.

47:23.634 --> 47:25.302
MY WIFE MADE
A KIDNEY PIE
FOR SUPPER,

47:25.469 --> 47:27.179
AND I AIN'T GONNA
MISS IT.

47:27.346 --> 47:28.931
LET'S GO. MOVE OUT!

47:55.749 --> 47:59.962
[CHIEF CHANTING
IN NATIVE LANGUAGE]
